.TH ILIB-FRAGGRAPH 1 "June 2026" "ilib @ILIB_VERSION@" "Ilib Manual"
.SH NAME
ilib-fraggraph \- graph a player's frags from QuakeWorld frag logs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ilib-fraggraph
.RI [ -gif | -png | -ppm | -jpeg | -bmp ]
.I player
.I fraglog
.RI [ fraglog ...]
.B >
.I out.img
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ilib-fraggraph
parses one or more QuakeWorld frag log files and writes an image graphing the
named
.IR player 's
frag activity to standard output.
.PP
The
.I player
name is matched case-sensitively. If the player is not found in the logs the
tool reports the problem rather than crashing.
.PP
The output format defaults to GIF; pass
.BR -png ", " -ppm ", " -jpeg " or " -bmp
to choose another (whichever codecs the library was built with).
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
ilib-fraggraph -png "Player1" frag.log > player1.png
.fi
.RE
.SH NOTES
This is a historical client tool retained as a worked example of using the
Ilib drawing and graphing API on parsed log data.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ilib-webreprt (1)
.PP
Full API documentation: https://craigk5n.github.io/ilib/
